It means the national flag will be flown at half-mast until the ceremony on 22 February, and South African police will provide ceremonial pomp on the day. The special official funeral category two is usually accorded to spouses of serving President and Deputy President, deputy ministers, Deputy Speaker of National Assembly, permanent Deputy Chairperson of the National Council of provinces, Deputy Chief Justice and the President of the Supreme Court of Appeal. Ramaphosa in January declared an official funeral category two for business leader, Dr Richard Maponya. Shabalala rose to fame as the founder and director of choral group Ladysmith Black Mambazo, which won five Grammy awards.

--BBC-- President @CyrilRamaphosa has declared a Special Official Funeral Category 2 in honour of Mr Joseph Shabalala, the late founder of choral group Ladysmith Black Mambazo.Mr Shabalala, aged 78, passed away on 11 February 2020 following extended illness. https://t.co/jJ5SNO2X45